5 By: Representative Rye
6 By: Senator D. Wallace
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND ARKANSAS MUSIC APPRECIATION DAY; TO
10 CHANGE THE DATE ON WHICH ARKANSAS MUSIC APPRECIATION
11 DAY IS CELEBRATED; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND ARKANSAS MUSIC APPRECIATION
16 DAY; AND TO CHANGE THE DATE ON WHICH
17 ARKANSAS MUSIC APPRECIATION DAY IS
18 CELEBRATED.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings.
23 The General Assembly finds that:
24 (1) Arkansas musicians are important to the cultural history of
25 the state;
26 (2) Arkansas musicians have made and continue to make important
27 contributions to music in this state and beyond and deserve recognition; and
28 (3) Arkansas Music Appreciation Day should be celebrated in the
29 state by encouraging Arkansas musicians to come to the State Capitol Building
30 each March 1 to increase public appreciation of Arkansas's contributions to
31 music by playing music in the State Capitol Building rotunda.
32
33 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 1-5-117(b), concerning Arkansas Music
34 Appreciation Day, is amended to read as follows:
35 (b) September March 1 of each year shall be known as “Arkansas Music
36 Appreciation Day” to honor the contributions of Arkansas musicians.
