1
2 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 1-5-117(d), concerning Arkansas Music
3 Appreciation Day, is amended to read as follows:
4 (d) Each year before September March 1, the Governor shall issue a
5 proclamation proclaiming September March 1 as Arkansas Music Appreciation Day
6 and in the proclamation shall:
7 (1) Comment on the significance of the contributions that
8 Arkansas musicians have made to the nation's music; and
9 (2) Call upon the citizens of the state to observe Arkansas
10 Music Appreciation Day.
